		{
			"post_id": 1488944437,
			"body": "The day that a performant ZeroNet Android app is published, I will seed 24/7 and I bet many others will as well. Also, I think ZeroNet use will skyrocket as most social networking activity of popular services is mobile now.\n\nI appreciate the existence of ZeroNet-Kivy, but it's too slow on my Nexus 6p.\n\nOne common demand is that a future official app has mesh networking protocol in it. I can see tremendous speeds in using half gigabit symmetric Wi-Fi ac. Nofish is well aware and I've even linked them to mesh networking SDKs. I and a few others proposed someone develop Meshcoin, but I myself am not sure how it will work.\n\nIf we are to gain any of this, then we have to tell our closely tied software developer friends about ZeroNet, these ideas, and provide the funding ourselves. I will help make it a career for Nofish and whomever claims bug bounties once my monthly budget is established. It will be hefty, monthly donations, too.",
